bonding chemical occurs naturally within us and is stimulated during sex, childbirth, and breastfeeding. For a long time, the chemical has been known to promote social bonding, trust, and even altruism. Now, scientists at the North Carolina university in America say it could also incite spirituality in men too. Vanguard New research conducted by Christopher West has proven that having sex could spur some sort of connection with divinity in us as human beings. November 2, 2019 In "News" Marvin Gaye’s “Sexual Healing”, Betty Wright’s “Tonight is the Night” and Madonna’s “Justify My Love” have one thing in common. Their lyrics are raunchy but powerfully emotive. They are songs widely acknowledged by millions across the world for their graphic illustration and exposition about sex. July 28, 2018 In "Health" Sex has no barrier. No matter the differences between the partners involved, race, colour, age, or class, sex dissolves them instantly. It needs no interpreter as sex speaks a universal language and aims to achieve same goal anywhere in the world. And no matter what name we want to call… May 14, 2016 In "News"